│ The core issue is a bug in the SLP vectorizer's horizontal reduction logic, where it attempts to delete an instruction that still has users. The simplest and most common fix for this   │
│ class of bug is to add a check to ensure that any intermediate value `Val` being considered for the reduction chain does not have more than one user. If it does, the reduction attempt  │
│ should be aborted.                                                                                                                                                                       │
